.....................................................................HTML CODE..............................................................................

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Document</title>
   <style>
    .class-1 a{
      color : inherit;
    }
     
    .class-2 a{
      color : initial;
    } 
     
    .class-3 a{
      color : unset;
    } 
   </style>
</head>
<body>
  
<ul>
  <li>default <a href="">link </a> color </li>
  <li class="class-1">inherited <a href="">link </a> color </li>
  <li class="class-2">initial <a href="">link </a> color </li>
  <li class="class-3">unset <a href="">link </a> color </li>
</ul>

</body>
</html>

.....................................................................css code................................................................................

/*
As you can see the default value of the text in first li is black and the link color is purple(without adding any style's)
*/

/*NOW LET'S ADD SOME STYLE IN INHERITANCE*/

/*
As you can see after inheritance the color of the link in second li(the one which is having class-1 as the class inheritate the color black rather than purple)

black bcz main html tag color was black...
*/

/*LETS SEE IF WE CAN CHANGE THE BLACK COLOR DEFAULT PROPERTY*/
/*use the style on body tag*/

body{
  color : yellow;
}

/*
LETS SEE INITIAL NOW...
THE INITIAL COLOR VALUE OF THE CHROME BROWSER IS BLACK
*/

/*
As you can see after using the initial, the color changes to the black not yellow,bcz the default or initial color of the chrome browser is black
*/

/*
if you search on google color property,there it will show
              "INHERITANCE : YES"
that means if you use unset the color will be yellow not the default one which is black  
*/
